🛡️ RCA (Root Cause Analysis) & Defense-in-Depth

Root Cause:
Service accounts utilizing weak, human-generated passwords combined with legacy RC4 encryption (encryption type 23).

Remediation Strategy:

Implement gMSA (Group Managed Service Accounts): AD automatically rotates these passwords with complex, 120-character strings, making them mathematically impossible to crack offline.

Enforce Strong Service Account Passwords: If gMSA cannot be used, passwords must be >25 random characters.

Disable RC4 Encryption: Force Kerberos to use AES-256 (encryption type 18). Hashcat cracking speeds for AES-256 are drastically slower than RC4.

